  "body": "I'm doing some hacks with geth, a panic was generated and I've been investigating a litte...\r\n\r\nderiveSigner (core/types/transaction.go#L43) does not set the `chainIdMul` field,\r\n\r\n`return EIP155Signer{chainId: deriveChainId(V)}`\r\n\r\nand this field is requiered in PublicKey(tx *Transaction)  (core/types/transaction_signing.go#L139)\r\n\r\n`V := byte(new(big.Int).Sub(tx.data.V, s.chainIdMul).Uint64() - 35)`\r\n\r\nThe stack trace for that is:\r\n\r\n  Transaction.String()\r\n  -> deriveSigner()\r\n  -> Sender(signer Signer, tx *Transaction) \r\n  ---> EIP155Signer.PublicKey(tx *Transaction)\r\n\r\nso, changing deriveSigner to:\r\n\r\n`return NewEIP155Signer(deriveChainId(V))`\r\n\r\nsolves the issue.\r\n\r\nI don't know it has some effect on production enviroments, nonetheless maybe\r\nmaintainers could check it.",
